cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.PL

The paper discusses the intersection of data-parallel and eventually consistent distributed systems, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on distributed computing and coordination-free computation suggests that cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with data structures and algorithms, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DB (Databases). The use of novel techniques and theoretical study suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.PL (Programming Languages).
